Class IElementType

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.psi.tree.IElementType
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BuildoutCfgElementType, CustomHighlighterTokenType.CustomElementType, CustomParsingType, GroovyDocElementType, GroovyElementType, IDTDElementType, IgnoreElementType, IgnoreTokenType, IJavaDocElementType, IJavaElementType, IJspElementType, ILazyParseableElementType, IStubElementType, IXmlElementType, JqlElementType, JsonElementType, JsonTokenType, ManifestElementType, ManifestTokenType, MarkdownElementType, PrattTokenType, PropertiesElementType, PyElementType, RegExpElementType, RestElementType, RncElementType, ScopeTokenType, ShCompositeElementType, ShTokenType, SPIElementType, TextMateElementType, TokenWrapper, XPathElementType, YAMLElementType

    public class IElementType
extends java.lang.Object
    Interface for token types returned from lexical analysis and for types of nodes in the AST tree. All used element types are added to a registry which can be enumerated or accessed by index.
    See Also:
    Lexer.getTokenType(), ASTNode.getElementType()

      • IElementType

        protected IElementType(java.lang.String debugName,
                       Language language,
                       boolean register)
        Allows to construct element types for some temporary purposes without registering them. This is not default behavior and not recommended. A lot of other functionality (e.g. TokenSet) won't work with such element types. Please use IElementType(String, Language) unless you know what you're doing.

      • isLeftBound

        public boolean isLeftBound()
        Controls whitespace balancing behavior of PsiBuilder.

        By default, empty composite elements (containing no children) are bounded to the right (previous) neighbour, forming following tree: 

          [previous_element]
  [whitespace]
  [empty_element]
    <empty>
  [next_element]

        Left-bound elements are bounded to the left (next) neighbour instead: 

          [previous_element]
  [empty_element]
    <empty>
  [whitespace]
  [next_element]

        See com.intellij.lang.impl.PsiBuilderImpl.prepareLightTree() for details.

        Returns:
        true if empty elements of this type should be bound to the left.
